ax` for `redis-cart-0`.\n   - These metrics of Redis Service (`rrt` reflects \"Round Trip Time\") indicate an abnormal increase, aligning with the suspected cause.\n   \n3. **Node and Pod Analysis:**\n   - No significant pod-related or node-wide issues other than some memory usage reductions, which are not directly linked to the drastic increase in Redis Service response times.\n\n4. **Recalibrated Hypothesis:**\n   - The significant increase in Redis Service's `rrt` supports the hypothesis of Redis Service being the bottleneck due to potentially excessive load or resource exhaustion leading to performance degradation.\n\n### Conclusion\nGiven the metrics indicating an extreme increase in response time specifically related to the Redis Service (`rrt` and `rrt_max`), I SUPPORT the hypothesis that the root cause of the fault is extreme response time escalation in the Redis Service.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"rrt\", \"rrt_max\", \"node_memory_usage_rate\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis-cart-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Redis Service's response time (`rrt`, `rrt_max`) escalated drastically, indicating a service bottleneck.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Response time increased from ~1739.74ms (normal) to ~39828.0ms (fault).\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"}
